                    <!-- Section: UPI Flow Architecture -->
                    <div class="seamless-section" id="sm-architecture">
                        <h2>UPI Flow Architecture</h2>
                        <p>Understanding the complete UPI payment flow between all parties involved.</p>
                        <div class="sm-flow-diagram">
                            <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-icon">&#128100;</div><div>Customer</div></div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-icon">&#127970;</div><div>Merchant Server</div></div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-step highlight"><div class="sm-flow-icon">&#9889;</div><div>PayU API</div></div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-icon">&#128241;</div><div>UPI App</div></div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                            <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-icon">&#9989;</div><div>Response</div></div>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Detailed Flow Steps</h3>
                        <div class="sm-timeline">
                            <div class="sm-timeline-item">
                                <div class="sm-timeline-marker">1</div>
                                <div class="sm-timeline-content">
                                    <strong>Customer initiates payment</strong>
                                    <p>Customer selects UPI on merchant's checkout page and optionally enters VPA or selects UPI app.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-timeline-item">
                                <div class="sm-timeline-marker">2</div>
                                <div class="sm-timeline-content">
                                    <strong>Merchant server generates hash</strong>
                                    <p>Server computes SHA-512 hash using <code>key|txnid|amount|productinfo|firstname|email|udf1-5||||||salt</code></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-timeline-item">
                                <div class="sm-timeline-marker">3</div>
                                <div class="sm-timeline-content">
                                    <strong>POST to PayU _payment API</strong>
                                    <p>Merchant server sends payment request with <code>pg=UPI</code>, <code>bankcode=INTENT</code>, and <code>txn_s2s_flow=4</code>.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-timeline-item">
                                <div class="sm-timeline-marker">4</div>
                                <div class="sm-timeline-content">
                                    <strong>PayU returns deeplink</strong>
                                    <p>PayU responds with a UPI deeplink URL. Merchant generates QR code from this deeplink or redirects to UPI app.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-timeline-item">
                                <div class="sm-timeline-marker">5</div>
                                <div class="sm-timeline-content">
                                    <strong>Customer approves on UPI app</strong>
                                    <p>Customer scans QR or opens UPI app, enters PIN and approves the payment.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-timeline-item">
                                <div class="sm-timeline-marker">6</div>
                                <div class="sm-timeline-content">
                                    <strong>PayU sends callback / Merchant polls status</strong>
                                    <p>PayU sends S2S callback to surl/furl. Merchant should also poll verify API for confirmation.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sm-next-btn-wrapper">
                            <button class="button" onclick="smNavTo(document.querySelector('[data-section=sm-upiflow]'), 'sm-upiflow')">Next: UPI Intent Flow &rarr;</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>



                    <!-- Section: UPI Intent Flow -->
                    <div class="seamless-section" id="sm-upiflow">
                        <h2>UPI Intent Flow</h2>

                        <!-- UPI Simulator App Banner -->
                        <div class="sm-info-box" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
                            <div style="font-size:2rem;line-height:1;">&#128241;</div>
                            <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
                                <strong>PayU UPI Intent Simulator App</strong>
                                <p style="margin:0.25rem 0 0;">To test UPI Intent or complete UPI transactions in the sandbox environment, install the PayU UPI Simulator app on your Android device.</p>
                            </div>
                            <a href="https://github.com/payu-india/PayU-UPI-Intent-Simulator-App/blob/main/PayU_UPI_Simulator_v4(1.0.2)-release.apk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button sm-btn-primary" style="text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;padding:0.65rem 1.25rem !important;font-size:0.9rem !important;">Download APK &darr;</a>
                        </div>

                        <!-- GUIDE: Overview -->
                        <div class="sm-step-guide">
                            <div class="sm-guide-overview">
                                <h3>Overview</h3>
                                <p>PayU supports three types of UPI Intent flows for initiating payments. All three use the same <code>_payment</code> API with <code>pg=UPI</code> and <code>txn_s2s_flow=4</code> &mdash; the difference lies in the <code>bankcode</code> and how you handle the response deeplink on the customer's device.</p>
                                <ul style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
                                    <li><strong>Generic Intent</strong> &mdash; Works with any UPI app via QR code scanning (best for web)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Specific Intent</strong> &mdash; Targets a specific UPI app like Google Pay or PhonePe</li>
                                    <li><strong>Smart Intent</strong> &mdash; Auto-detects the best UPI app on the customer's device (required on Android per NPCI)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Documentation Link -->
                            <a href="https://docs.payu.in/docs/upi-intent-server-to-server" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="sm-docs-banner">
                                <div class="sm-docs-banner-icon">&#128214;</div>
                                <div class="sm-docs-banner-body">
                                    <div class="sm-docs-banner-title">PayU Official Documentation <span class="sm-docs-badge">Docs</span></div>
                                    <div class="sm-docs-banner-desc">UPI Intent with S2S Integration &mdash; Complete integration guide with <code>_payment</code> API, bankcode options, deeplink handling &amp; response parameters.</div>
                                </div>
                                <span class="sm-docs-banner-arrow">&rarr;</span>
                            </a>

                            <!-- Prerequisites -->
                            <div class="sm-guide-prereqs">
                                <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
                                <div class="sm-prereq-list">
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>Merchant Key &amp; Salt</strong><br>Your PayU test/UAT credentials</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>UPI S2S Enabled</strong><br>UPI payment mode with S2S flow enabled on your account</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>QR Library (Web)</strong><br>A QR code generation library for rendering deeplinks</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>Deep Link Handling (Mobile)</strong><br>Intent handling on Android / URL scheme on iOS</div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Flow Diagram -->
                            <div class="sm-guide-flow">
                                <h3>How It Works</h3>
                                <div class="sm-flow-diagram">
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">1</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Merchant<br><small>POST _payment</small></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">2</div><div class="sm-flow-label">PayU S2S<br><small>Returns deeplink</small></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">3</div><div class="sm-flow-label">UPI Deeplink<br><small>QR / App Launch</small></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">4</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Customer<br><small>Pays via UPI</small></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">5</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Callback<br><small>surl / furl</small></div></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Step-by-Step -->
                            <div class="sm-guide-steps">
                                <h3>Step-by-Step Guide</h3>
                                <div class="sm-numbered-steps">
                                    <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">1</div><div class="sm-step-content"><strong>Choose an intent type</strong><p>Decide between Generic (QR), Specific (target app), or Smart (auto-detect). This determines the <code>bankcode</code> you send.</p></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">2</div><div class="sm-step-content"><strong>Send the payment request</strong><p>POST to <code>_payment</code> with <code>pg=UPI</code>, <code>txn_s2s_flow=4</code>, and your chosen <code>bankcode</code>. Use the <strong>Initiate Payment</strong> form (next step) to test.</p></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">3</div><div class="sm-step-content"><strong>Extract the deeplink from the response</strong><p>PayU returns <code>intentURIData</code> (a <code>upi://pay?...</code> URL) or <code>acsTemplate</code> (base64 HTML). Extract the deeplink URI.</p></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">4</div><div class="sm-step-content"><strong>Present to customer</strong><p><strong>Web:</strong> Convert deeplink to QR code. <strong>Android:</strong> Fire an <code>ACTION_VIEW</code> intent. <strong>iOS:</strong> Open the URL scheme for the target app.</p></div></div>
                                    <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">5</div><div class="sm-step-content"><strong>Poll &amp; handle callback</strong><p>Poll <code>check_payment</code> while waiting. PayU posts the final result to your <code>surl</code> (success) or <code>furl</code> (failure).</p></div></div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                        </div>

                        <!-- Intent Type Tabs -->
                        <h3>Intent Types &mdash; Deep Dive</h3>
                        <div class="sm-tab-group">
                            <button class="sm-tab active" data-tab="generic" onclick="smSwitchUPITab(this, 'upi-generic')"><span style="margin-right:0.4rem;">&#x25A3;</span>Generic Intent</button>
                            <button class="sm-tab" data-tab="specific" onclick="smSwitchUPITab(this, 'upi-specific')"><span style="margin-right:0.4rem;">&#x25C9;</span>Specific Intent</button>
                            <button class="sm-tab" data-tab="smart" onclick="smSwitchUPITab(this, 'upi-smart')"><span style="margin-right:0.4rem;">&#x2726;</span>Smart Intent</button>
                                    </div>

                        <!-- ===== Generic Intent ===== -->
                        <div class="sm-upi-tab-content active" id="upi-generic">
                            <h3>&#x25A3; Generic UPI Intent</h3>
                            <div class="sm-info-box">
                                <strong>How it works:</strong> Generates a UPI deeplink URL that you convert into a <strong>QR code</strong>. Any UPI app on the customer's phone can scan the QR to pay. Best for <strong>desktop web</strong> and cross-platform payments.
                                        </div>

                            <h4>Workflow</h4>
                            <div class="sm-flow-diagram" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">1</div><div class="sm-flow-label">POST<br><small>_payment API</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">2</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Extract<br><small>intentURIData</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">3</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Build<br><small>Deeplink</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">4</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Generate<br><small>QR Code</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">5</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Customer<br><small>Scans &amp; Pays</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">6</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Verify<br><small>Payment</small></div></div>
                                    </div>

                            <div class="sm-numbered-steps">
                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">1</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Send Payment Request</strong>
                                    <p>POST to <code>_payment</code> with these key parameters for Generic Intent:</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Generic Intent Parameters</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>pg=UPI
bankcode=INTENT
txn_s2s_flow=4
s2s_client_ip=10.200.12.12
s2s_device_info=Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64)</code></pre></div>
                                    <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;">Use the <strong>Initiate Payment</strong> form (next step) to test this &mdash; select <code>bankcode=INTENT</code>.</p>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">2</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Extract intentURIData from Response</strong>
                                    <p>If <code>metaData.unmappedStatus = "pending"</code>, extract <code>result.intentURIData</code> from the response.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Sample Response</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>{
  "metaData": {
    "txnId": "my_order_26075",
    "unmappedStatus": "pending"
  },
  "result": {
    "paymentId": "403993715535965242",
    "intentURIData": "pa=payutest@hdfcbank&amp;pn=Kumar&amp;tr=...&amp;am=1.00&amp;cu=INR",
    "acsTemplate": "PGh0bWw+PGJvZHk+Li4u..."
  }
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">3</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Build the Deeplink</strong>
                                    <p>Add the <code>upi://pay?</code> prefix to <code>intentURIData</code> to create a fully qualified UPI deeplink.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>JavaScript</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>const intentURIData = response.result.intentURIData;
const deeplink = "upi://pay?" + intentURIData;</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">4</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Generate QR Code</strong>
                                    <p>Convert the deeplink into a QR code and display it to the customer.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Node.js &ndash; QR Code</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>const QRCode = require('qrcode');
const deeplink = "upi://pay?" + response.result.intentURIData;
const qrDataURL = await QRCode.toDataURL(deeplink);
document.getElementById('qr-img').src = qrDataURL;</code></pre></div>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>HTML &ndash; qrcode.js (CDN)</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>&lt;script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/qrcode/build/qrcode.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;canvas id="qr-canvas"&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  QRCode.toCanvas(document.getElementById('qr-canvas'), deeplink, { width: 280 });
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">5</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Customer Scans QR &amp; Pays</strong>
                                    <p>The customer opens any UPI app, scans the QR code, and completes the payment. While waiting, <strong>poll</strong> the transaction status.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>JavaScript &ndash; Poll Status</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>async function pollPaymentStatus(txnId, interval = 5000) {
  const poll = setInterval(async () =&gt; {
    const status = await checkPaymentStatus(txnId);
    if (status !== 'pending') {
      clearInterval(poll);
      handlePaymentResult(status);
    }
  }, interval);
  setTimeout(() =&gt; clearInterval(poll), 300000);
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">6</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Verify the Payment</strong>
                                    <p>Always call <code>verify_payment</code> to confirm the final transaction status. Configure <strong>webhooks</strong> for server-to-server notifications.</p>
                                    <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;">Ref: <a href="https://docs.payu.in/docs/upi-intent-server-to-server" target="_blank" style="color:#1a7a5b;">PayU UPI Intent S2S Docs</a></p>
                                </div></div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                        <!-- ===== Specific Intent ===== -->
                        <div class="sm-upi-tab-content" id="upi-specific">
                            <h3>&#x25C9; Specific UPI Intent</h3>
                            <div class="sm-info-box">
                                <strong>How it works:</strong> Targets a <strong>specific UPI app</strong> (Google Pay, PhonePe, Paytm, etc.) by using its bank code. Best for <strong>mobile</strong> where you detect installed apps and let the customer choose.
                                        </div>
                            <div class="sm-info-box warning">
                                <strong>NPCI Mandate:</strong> All merchants must show a <strong>"Pay by any UPI App"</strong> option on Android alongside specific app options.
                                    </div>

                            <h4>Workflow</h4>
                            <div class="sm-flow-diagram" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">1</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Fetch<br><small>UPI Apps</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">2</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Get<br><small>Intent URI</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">3</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Extract<br><small>intentURIData</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">4</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Add Prefix<br><small>&amp; Launch</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">5</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Handle<br><small>Response</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">6</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Verify<br><small>Payment</small></div></div>
                        </div>

                            <div class="sm-numbered-steps">
                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">1</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Fetch List of UPI Apps on Device</strong>
                                    <p>Query the device for installed UPI apps to display on your checkout page.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Kotlin &ndash; Fetch UPI Apps</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>fun getUPIApps(context: Context): List&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; {
    val intent = Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW, Uri.parse("upi://pay"))
    val activities = context.packageManager
        .queryIntentActivities(intent, PackageManager.MATCH_DEFAULT_ONLY)
    return activities.map { info -&gt;
        val name = context.packageManager
            .getApplicationLabel(info.activityInfo.applicationInfo).toString()
        mapOf("appName" to name, "packageName" to info.activityInfo.packageName)
    }
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">2</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Get Intent URI from PayU</strong>
                                    <p>POST to <code>_payment</code> with <code>pg=UPI</code>, <code>txn_s2s_flow=4</code>, and the specific <code>bankcode</code> for the chosen app.</p>
                                    <h4 style="margin:0.75rem 0 0.5rem;font-size:0.88rem;">Supported Bank Codes</h4>
                                    <table class="sm-table" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
                                        <thead><tr><th>UPI App</th><th>Bank Code</th><th>Package Name (Android)</th></tr></thead>
                            <tbody>
                                            <tr><td>Google Pay</td><td><code>TEZ</code></td><td><code>com.google.android.apps.nbu.paisa.user</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>PhonePe</td><td><code>PHONEPE</code></td><td><code>com.phonepe.app</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>Paytm</td><td><code>PAYTM</code></td><td><code>net.one97.paytm</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>BHIM</td><td><code>BHIM</code></td><td><code>in.org.npci.upiapp</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>Amazon Pay</td><td><code>AMAZONPAY</code></td><td><code>in.amazon.mShop.android.shopping</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>CRED</td><td><code>CRED</code></td><td><code>com.dreamplug.androidapp</code></td></tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">3</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Extract Deeplink from Response</strong>
                                    <p>If <code>metaData.unmappedStatus = "pending"</code>, extract <code>result.intentURIData</code>. This is not a complete deeplink &mdash; you must add a platform-specific prefix.</p>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">4</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Add Platform Prefix &amp; Launch the App</strong>
                                    <p>Prepend a platform-specific prefix to <code>intentURIData</code> to build the final deeplink.</p>
                                    <table class="sm-table" style="margin:0.75rem 0;">
                                        <thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Prefix Format</th></tr></thead>
                                        <tbody>
                                            <tr><td>Android (Specific)</td><td><code>intent://pay?{data}#Intent;scheme=upi;package=&lt;pkg&gt;;end</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>iOS &mdash; PhonePe</td><td><code>phonepe://upi/pay?</code> + intentURIData</td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>iOS &mdash; Google Pay</td><td><code>gpay://upi/pay?</code> + intentURIData</td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>iOS &mdash; Paytm</td><td><code>paytm://upi/pay?</code> + intentURIData</td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>iOS &mdash; BHIM</td><td><code>bhim://upi/pay?</code> + intentURIData</td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>iOS &mdash; CRED</td><td><code>credpay://upi/pay?</code> + intentURIData</td></tr>
                                        </tbody>
                                    </table>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Kotlin &ndash; Launch Specific UPI App</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>fun launchUPIApp(activity: Activity, packageName: String, intentUri: String) {
    val intent = Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW)
    intent.setPackage(packageName)
    intent.data = Uri.parse("upi://pay?$intentUri")
    activity.startActivityForResult(intent, 101)
}</code></pre></div>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>iOS (Swift) &ndash; Open Specific App</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>let deeplink = "phonepe://upi/pay?" + intentURIData
if let url = URL(string: deeplink), UIApplication.shared.canOpenURL(url) {
    UIApplication.shared.open(url)
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">5</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Handle the UPI App Response</strong>
                                    <p>After the customer completes payment, handle the result in <code>onActivityResult</code>.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Kotlin &ndash; onActivityResult</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>override fun onActivityResult(requestCode: Int, resultCode: Int, data: Intent?) {
    super.onActivityResult(requestCode, resultCode, data)
    if (requestCode == 101) {
        val status = data?.getStringExtra("Status") ?: "unknown"
        verifyPayment(txnId) // Always verify regardless of status
    }
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">6</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Verify the Payment</strong>
                                    <p>Always call <code>verify_payment</code> to confirm the final transaction status. Do not rely solely on the UPI app callback.</p>
                                    <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;">Ref: <a href="https://docs.payu.in/docs/upi-intent-server-to-server" target="_blank" style="color:#1a7a5b;">PayU UPI Intent S2S Docs</a></p>
                                </div></div>
                                </div>
                                </div>

                        <!-- ===== Smart Intent ===== -->
                        <div class="sm-upi-tab-content" id="upi-smart">
                            <h3>&#x2726; Smart UPI Intent</h3>
                            <div class="sm-info-box">
                                <strong>How it works:</strong> Auto-detects UPI apps on the customer's device and lets the OS present an app chooser. Required on Android per <strong>NPCI mandate</strong>.
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-info-box warning">
                                <strong>NPCI Mandate</strong>
                                <ul style="margin:0.25rem 0 0;">
                                    <li><strong>Android:</strong> Must implement Smart Intent &mdash; "Pay by any UPI App" is mandatory</li>
                                    <li><strong>Web:</strong> Must use UPI Intent S2S to generate QR code instead of UPI Collect</li>
                                    <li><strong>iOS:</strong> Can use UPI Collect or app-specific deeplinks</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <h4>Workflow</h4>
                            <div class="sm-flow-diagram" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">1</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Update<br><small>Manifest</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">2</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Fetch<br><small>UPI Apps</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">3</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Get<br><small>Intent URI</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">4</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Add Prefix<br><small>&amp; Launch</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">5</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Handle<br><small>Response</small></div></div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                <div class="sm-flow-step"><div class="sm-flow-num">6</div><div class="sm-flow-label">Verify<br><small>Payment</small></div></div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="sm-numbered-steps">
                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">1</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Update Manifest File (One-Time &mdash; Android 11+)</strong>
                                    <p>Add UPI app package IDs to your <code>AndroidManifest.xml</code> so your app can detect installed UPI apps.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>AndroidManifest.xml</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>&lt;queries&gt;
    &lt;package android:name="com.google.android.apps.nbu.paisa.user"/&gt;  &lt;!-- Google Pay --&gt;
    &lt;package android:name="com.phonepe.app"/&gt;                         &lt;!-- PhonePe --&gt;
    &lt;package android:name="net.one97.paytm"/&gt;                         &lt;!-- Paytm --&gt;
    &lt;package android:name="in.org.npci.upiapp"/&gt;                      &lt;!-- BHIM --&gt;
    &lt;package android:name="in.amazon.mShop.android.shopping"/&gt;        &lt;!-- Amazon Pay --&gt;
    &lt;package android:name="com.dreamplug.androidapp"/&gt;                &lt;!-- CRED --&gt;
&lt;/queries&gt;</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">2</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Fetch List of UPI Apps on Device</strong>
                                    <p>Query the device for installed UPI apps to display on your checkout page or use the OS app chooser.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Kotlin &ndash; Fetch UPI Apps</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>fun getUPIApps(context: Context): List&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; {
    val intent = Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW, Uri.parse("upi://pay"))
    val activities = context.packageManager
        .queryIntentActivities(intent, PackageManager.MATCH_DEFAULT_ONLY)
    return activities.map { info -&gt;
        val name = context.packageManager
            .getApplicationLabel(info.activityInfo.applicationInfo).toString()
        mapOf("appName" to name, "packageName" to info.activityInfo.packageName)
    }
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">3</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Get Intent URI from PayU</strong>
                                    <p>POST to <code>_payment</code> with <code>pg=UPI</code>, <code>bankcode=INTENT</code>, <code>txn_s2s_flow=4</code>. Extract <code>result.intentURIData</code> when <code>unmappedStatus = "pending"</code>.</p>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">4</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Add Platform Prefix &amp; Launch UPI App</strong>
                                    <p>The <code>intentURIData</code> is <strong>not</strong> a complete deeplink. Prepend a platform-specific prefix:</p>
                                    <table class="sm-table" style="margin:0.75rem 0;">
                                        <thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Prefix Format</th></tr></thead>
                                        <tbody>
                                            <tr><td>Generic / QR / Web</td><td><code>upi://pay?</code> + intentURIData</td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>Android (App Chooser)</td><td><code>intent://pay?{data}#Intent;scheme=upi;end</code></td></tr>
                                            <tr><td>Android (Specific)</td><td><code>intent://pay?{data}#Intent;scheme=upi;package=&lt;pkg&gt;;end</code></td></tr>
                                        </tbody>
                                    </table>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Kotlin &ndash; Smart Intent (OS Chooser)</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>// "Pay by any UPI App" - no package set, OS shows app chooser
val intent = Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW)
intent.data = Uri.parse("upi://pay?$intentUri")
activity.startActivityForResult(intent, 101)</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">5</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Handle the UPI App Response</strong>
                                    <p>After the customer completes payment, handle the result in <code>onActivityResult</code>.</p>
                                    <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><div class="sm-code-header"><span>Kotlin &ndash; onActivityResult</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div><pre><code>override fun onActivityResult(requestCode: Int, resultCode: Int, data: Intent?) {
    super.onActivityResult(requestCode, resultCode, data)
    if (requestCode == 101) {
        val status = data?.getStringExtra("Status") ?: "unknown"
        verifyPayment(txnId) // Always verify regardless of status
    }
}</code></pre></div>
                                </div></div>

                                <div class="sm-step"><div class="sm-step-num">6</div><div class="sm-step-content">
                                    <strong>Verify the Payment</strong>
                                    <p>Always call <code>verify_payment</code> to confirm the transaction status. Do <strong>not</strong> rely solely on the UPI app callback.</p>
                                    <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;">Ref: <a href="https://docs.payu.in/docs/upi-intent-server-to-server" target="_blank" style="color:#1a7a5b;">PayU UPI Intent S2S Docs</a></p>
                                </div></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Testing Tip -->
                        <div class="sm-info-box" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
                            <strong>&#128161; Testing Intent Flows</strong>
                            <p>Use the <strong>Initiate Payment</strong> form (next step) to test Intent flows &mdash; select the appropriate <code>bankcode</code> (INTENT, TEZ, PHONEPE, or PAYTM) from the dropdown. All intent types use the same <code>_payment</code> API.</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="sm-next-btn-wrapper">
                            <button class="button" onclick="openSeamlessFlow('sm-payment')">Next: Initiate Payment &rarr;</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Section: UPI One-Time Payment -->
                    <div class="seamless-section" id="sm-payment">
                        <h2>UPI One-Time Payment (S2S)</h2>

                        <!-- GUIDE: Overview -->
                        <div class="sm-step-guide">
                            <div class="sm-guide-overview">
                                <h3>Overview</h3>
                                <p>The UPI One-Time Payment API lets you initiate a single UPI payment via PayU's Server-to-Server (S2S) flow. You POST payment details to the <code>_payment</code> endpoint with <code>pg=UPI</code>, and PayU returns a deeplink or redirect for the customer to authorize the payment in their UPI app.</p>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Prerequisites -->
                            <div class="sm-guide-prereqs">
                                <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
                                <div class="sm-prereq-list">
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>Merchant Key &amp; Salt</strong><br>Your PayU test/UAT credentials</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>UPI Enabled</strong><br>UPI payment mode activated on your PayU account</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">&#10003;</span>
                                        <div><strong>Hash Generated</strong><br>SHA-512 payment hash computed server-side</div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Flow Diagram -->
                            <div class="sm-guide-flow">
                                <h3>How It Works</h3>
                                <div class="sm-flow-diagram">
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step">
                                        <div class="sm-flow-num">1</div>
                                        <div class="sm-flow-label">Merchant<br><small>Sends payment</small></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step">
                                        <div class="sm-flow-num">2</div>
                                        <div class="sm-flow-label">PayU API<br><small>_payment</small></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step">
                                        <div class="sm-flow-num">3</div>
                                        <div class="sm-flow-label">UPI Switch<br><small>Routes txn</small></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step">
                                        <div class="sm-flow-num">4</div>
                                        <div class="sm-flow-label">Customer App<br><small>Authorizes</small></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
                                    <div class="sm-flow-step">
                                        <div class="sm-flow-num">5</div>
                                        <div class="sm-flow-label">Complete<br><small>Callback</small></div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Step-by-Step -->
                            <div class="sm-guide-steps">
                                <h3>Step-by-Step Guide</h3>
                                <div class="sm-numbered-steps">
                                    <div class="sm-step">
                                        <div class="sm-step-num">1</div>
                                        <div class="sm-step-content">
                                            <strong>Collect payment details</strong>
                                            <p>Gather the transaction amount, product info, and customer details (name, email, phone). Generate a unique <code>txnid</code> (max 25 chars).</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-step">
                                        <div class="sm-step-num">2</div>
                                        <div class="sm-step-content">
                                            <strong>Generate the payment hash</strong>
                                            <p>Compute <code>sha512(key|txnid|amount|productinfo|firstname|email|udf1|udf2|udf3|udf4|udf5||||||salt)</code> on your server. Never expose salt client-side.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-step">
                                        <div class="sm-step-num">3</div>
                                        <div class="sm-step-content">
                                            <strong>POST to PayU _payment endpoint</strong>
                                            <p>Send all parameters including <code>pg=UPI</code>, <code>bankcode</code> (INTENT/TEZ/PHONEPE/PAYTM), and <code>txn_s2s_flow=4</code> to <code>https://test.payu.in/_payment</code>.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-step">
                                        <div class="sm-step-num">4</div>
                                        <div class="sm-step-content">
                                            <strong>Handle the S2S response</strong>
                                            <p>If <code>unmappedStatus=pending</code> with <code>intentURIData</code>, generate a QR code from the deeplink. If <code>acsTemplate</code> is returned, decode the base64 HTML and render it.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-step">
                                        <div class="sm-step-num">5</div>
                                        <div class="sm-step-content">
                                            <strong>Poll for payment status</strong>
                                            <p>Use <code>check_payment</code> API to poll until the transaction moves to <code>success</code> or <code>failure</code>. PayU also sends a callback to your <code>surl</code>/<code>furl</code>.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- API Reference -->
                        <h3>API Reference</h3>
                        <table class="sm-table">
                            <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr><td><code>key</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; Merchant key provided by PayU during onboarding</td><td>JPg****f</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>txnid</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; The transaction ID is a reference number for a specific order generated by the merchant</td><td>ypl938459435</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>amount</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; The payment amount for the transaction</td><td>10.00</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>productinfo</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; A brief description of the product</td><td>iPhone</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>firstname</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; The first name of the customer</td><td>Ashish</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>lastname</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; The last name of the customer</td><td>Kumar</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>email</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; The email address of the customer</td><td>test@gmail.com</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>phone</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; The phone number of the customer</td><td>9876543210</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>zipcode</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; Billing address zip code. Character Limit&ndash;20</td><td>400004</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>surl</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; Success URL; PayU redirects here if the transaction is successful</td><td>https://test.payu.in/admin/test_response</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>furl</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; Failure URL; PayU redirects here if the transaction fails</td><td>https://test.payu.in/admin/test_response</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>hash</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; SHA-512 payment hash (auto-computed)</td><td><em>(computed)</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>pg</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory (S2S)</span></td><td>String &mdash; Defines the payment category. Post <code>UPI</code></td><td>UPI</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>bankcode</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory (S2S)</span></td><td>String &mdash; Unique bank code for UPI payment option: INTENT (generic/QR), TEZ (Google Pay), PHONEPE, PAYTM, BHIM, AMAZONPAY, CRED</td><td>INTENT</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>txn_s2s_flow</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-conditional">Conditional</span></td><td>Integer &mdash; Parameter to enable S2S flow. Must be <code>4</code> for Legacy Decoupled flow (UPI Intent)</td><td>4</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>s2s_client_ip</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; Source IP of the customer. Required for UPI Intent flow</td><td>10.200.12.12</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>s2s_device_info</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-mandatory">Mandatory</span></td><td>String &mdash; Customer agent's device information. Required for UPI Intent flow</td><td>Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64)</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>vpa</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-conditional">Conditional</span></td><td>String &mdash; Customer's VPA handle. Mandatory for UPI Collect flow</td><td>customer@upi</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>udf1</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-conditional">Conditional</span></td><td>String &mdash; Mandatory if AD bank requests this detail. Must contain Buyer's PAN and DOB: <code>PAN||DOB</code></td><td>AAAPZ1234C||22/08/1972</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>udf2</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span></td><td>String &mdash; User-defined field 2</td><td></td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>udf3</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-conditional">Conditional</span></td><td>String &mdash; Mandatory if AD bank requests this detail. Must contain Invoice ID and Merchant Name: <code>InvoiceID||MerchantName</code></td><td>INV-123_1231||MerchantName</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>udf4</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span></td><td>String &mdash; User-defined field 4</td><td></td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>udf5</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span></td><td>String &mdash; User-defined field 5</td><td></td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>address1</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span> <small style="color:#64748b;">(recommended)</small></td><td>String &mdash; Billing address line 1. Helpful for fraud detection and chargebacks</td><td>34 Saikripa-Estate, Tilak Nagar</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>address2</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span> <small style="color:#64748b;">(recommended)</small></td><td>String &mdash; Billing address line 2</td><td></td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>city</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span> <small style="color:#64748b;">(recommended)</small></td><td>String &mdash; Billing city. Recommended for higher approval rate</td><td>Mumbai</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>state</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span> <small style="color:#64748b;">(recommended)</small></td><td>String &mdash; Billing state. Recommended for higher approval rate</td><td>Maharashtra</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>country</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span> <small style="color:#64748b;">(recommended)</small></td><td>String &mdash; Billing country. Recommended for higher approval rate</td><td>India</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>upiAppName</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span></td><td>String &mdash; Name of the UPI app selected by the customer on checkout</td><td>gpay/phonepe/paytm/qr/amazonpay</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>udf_params</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span></td><td>JSON String &mdash; Additional UDF parameters (udf6&ndash;udf10)</td><td>{"udf7":"asdf","udf8":"12"}</td></tr>
                                <tr><td><code>buyer_type_business</code></td><td><span class="sm-badge-optional">Optional</span></td><td>Binary &mdash; Send <code>1</code> if the buyer is a business (B2B cross-border). Default is <code>0</code>. Included in hash if posted</td><td>1</td></tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <div class="sm-code-block" style="margin-top:1rem;">
                            <div class="sm-code-header"><span>Hash Formula</span><button onclick="smCopyCode(this)">Copy</button></div>
                            <pre><code>sha512(key|txnid|amount|productinfo|firstname|email|udf1|udf2|udf3|udf4|udf5||||||salt)
Example: sha512(a4vGC2|TXN_123|10.00|iPhone|Ashish|test@gmail.com|ABCDE1234F||1990-01-01||INV123456||MerchantName||||||||hKvGJP28d2ZUuCRz5BnDag58QBdCxBli)</code></pre>
                        </div>

