                    <!-- ============================================ -->
                    <!-- ACS TEMPLATE DECODER TOOL                    -->
                    <!-- ============================================ -->
                    <div class="seamless-section" id="sm-cards-acs-tool">
                        <h2 style="margin-bottom:0.25rem;">ACS Template Decoder</h2>
                        <p style="color:#64748b;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Decode and inspect the <code>acsTemplate</code> returned by PayU&rsquo;s payment API for 3D Secure authentication.</p>

                        <div class="sm-step-guide">
                            <div class="sm-guide-overview">
                                <h3>What is <code>acsTemplate</code>?</h3>
                                <p>When you make a card payment via S2S (server-to-server), PayU returns an <code>acsTemplate</code> in the response. This is a <strong>base64-encoded HTML page</strong> that, when decoded and rendered in the browser, auto-submits a form to redirect the customer to the bank&rsquo;s 3DS (3D Secure) authentication page where they enter their OTP.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sm-guide-prereqs">
                                <h3>When do you get it?</h3>
                                <div class="sm-prereq-list">
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">1</span>
                                        <div><strong>S2S Payment</strong><br>Any <code>_payment</code> API call</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">2</span>
                                        <div><strong>Response field</strong><br><code>result.acsTemplate</code></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="sm-prereq-item">
                                        <span class="sm-prereq-icon">3</span>
                                        <div><strong>Encoding</strong><br>Base64 string</div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- How it works -->
                        <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
                            <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">How 3DS Redirect Works</h3>
                            <div class="sm-card-grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));">
                                <div class="sm-card" style="text-align:center;">
                                    <div style="font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#9312;</div>
                                    <h4>Payment API Call</h4>
                                    <p>You send <code>_payment</code> request with card details. PayU processes and returns response with <code>acsTemplate</code>.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="sm-card" style="text-align:center;">
                                    <div style="font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#9313;</div>
                                    <h4>Decode Base64</h4>
                                    <p>The <code>acsTemplate</code> is a base64-encoded HTML string. Decode it using <code>atob()</code> in JS or <code>base64_decode()</code> in PHP.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="sm-card" style="text-align:center;">
                                    <div style="font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#9314;</div>
                                    <h4>Render HTML</h4>
                                    <p>Write the decoded HTML to a new browser window or page. The HTML contains an auto-submitting form that redirects to the bank.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="sm-card" style="text-align:center;">
                                    <div style="font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#9315;</div>
                                    <h4>Bank 3DS Page</h4>
                                    <p>Customer enters OTP on the bank&rsquo;s page. After authentication, the bank redirects back to your <code>surl</code>/<code>furl</code>.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Decoder Tool -->
                        <div style="margin-top:2rem;padding:1.5rem;background:#f8fafc;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
                            <h3 style="margin:0 0 0.5rem;color:#334155;">Try It &mdash; Decode ACS Template</h3>
                            <p style="margin:0 0 1rem;color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem;">Paste the raw <code>acsTemplate</code> value (base64 string) from the payment API response below.</p>

                            <div class="sm-form-group" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
                                <label style="font-weight:600;">ACS Template (base64) <span class="required">*</span></label>
                                <textarea id="acsDecoderInput" rows="6" placeholder="Paste the base64-encoded acsTemplate string here..." style="width:100%;padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid #d1d5db;border-radius:8px;font-family:monospace;font-size:0.85rem;resize:vertical;"></textarea>
                            </div>

                            <div style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                                <button class="button sm-btn-primary" onclick="smAcsDecoderDecode()">&#128269; Decode &amp; Preview</button>
                                <button class="button" onclick="smAcsDecoderOpen()">&#128279; Open in New Tab</button>
                                <button class="button" onclick="smAcsDecoderClear()" style="background:#f1f5f9;color:#64748b;">Clear</button>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Decoded output -->
                            <div id="acsDecoderOutput" style="display:none;margin-top:1.25rem;">
                                <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
                                    <h4 style="margin:0;color:#10846D;">&#10003; Decoded HTML</h4>
                                    <button onclick="smCopyCode(this)" class="sm-copy-btn">Copy HTML</button>
                                </div>
                                <pre style="max-height:400px;overflow:auto;background:#1e293b;color:#e2e8f0;padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:0.82rem;line-height:1.6;"><code id="acsDecoderHtml"></code></pre>

                                <div style="margin-top:1rem;">
                                    <h4 style="margin:0 0 0.5rem;color:#334155;">Extracted Details</h4>
                                    <div id="acsDecoderDetails" class="sm-card-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr;"></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Error -->
                            <div id="acsDecoderError" style="display:none;margin-top:1rem;">
                                <div class="sm-info-box" style="border-left:4px solid #e53e3e;padding:0.75rem 1rem;background:rgba(229,62,62,0.06);">
                                    <strong style="color:#e53e3e;">&#10007; Decode Failed</strong>
                                    <p id="acsDecoderErrorMsg" style="margin:0.25rem 0 0;font-size:0.9rem;color:#666;"></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Code samples -->
                        <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
                            <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Code Samples &mdash; Decode &amp; Render</h3>
                            <div style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                                <button class="sm-phase-tab active" onclick="smSwitchAcsCodeTab(this,'js')">JavaScript</button>
                                <button class="sm-phase-tab" onclick="smSwitchAcsCodeTab(this,'php')">PHP</button>
                                <button class="sm-phase-tab" onclick="smSwitchAcsCodeTab(this,'python')">Python</button>
                                <button class="sm-phase-tab" onclick="smSwitchAcsCodeTab(this,'java')">Java</button>
                            </div>

                            <div id="acsCode-js" class="acs-code-panel" style="position:relative;">
                                <button onclick="smCopyCode(this)" class="sm-copy-btn" style="position:absolute;top:0.5rem;right:0.5rem;">Copy</button>
                                <pre style="background:#1e293b;color:#e2e8f0;padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:0.82rem;line-height:1.6;overflow-x:auto;"><code>// JavaScript &mdash; Decode and open in new window
var acsBase64 = response.result.acsTemplate;

// Step 1: Decode from Base64
var decodedHtml = atob(acsBase64);

// Step 2: Open in a new browser window/tab
var win = window.open('', '_blank');
win.document.open();
win.document.write(decodedHtml);
win.document.close();
// The HTML auto-submits a form &rarr; redirects to bank 3DS page</code></pre>
                            </div>

                            <div id="acsCode-php" class="acs-code-panel" style="display:none;position:relative;">
                                <button onclick="smCopyCode(this)" class="sm-copy-btn" style="position:absolute;top:0.5rem;right:0.5rem;">Copy</button>
                                <pre style="background:#1e293b;color:#e2e8f0;padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:0.82rem;line-height:1.6;overflow-x:auto;"><code>// PHP &mdash; Decode and render to browser
$acsBase64 = $response['result']['acsTemplate'];

// Step 1: Decode from Base64
$decodedHtml = base64_decode($acsBase64);

// Step 2: Output directly to browser (auto-submits to bank)
header('Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8');
echo $decodedHtml;
exit;</code></pre>
                            </div>

                            <div id="acsCode-python" class="acs-code-panel" style="display:none;position:relative;">
                                <button onclick="smCopyCode(this)" class="sm-copy-btn" style="position:absolute;top:0.5rem;right:0.5rem;">Copy</button>
                                <pre style="background:#1e293b;color:#e2e8f0;padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:0.82rem;line-height:1.6;overflow-x:auto;"><code># Python (Flask) &mdash; Decode and return as HTML response
import base64
from flask import Response

acs_base64 = response['result']['acsTemplate']

# Step 1: Decode from Base64
decoded_html = base64.b64decode(acs_base64).decode('utf-8')

# Step 2: Return as HTML response (auto-submits to bank)
return Response(decoded_html, content_type='text/html')</code></pre>
                            </div>

                            <div id="acsCode-java" class="acs-code-panel" style="display:none;position:relative;">
                                <button onclick="smCopyCode(this)" class="sm-copy-btn" style="position:absolute;top:0.5rem;right:0.5rem;">Copy</button>
                                <pre style="background:#1e293b;color:#e2e8f0;padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:0.82rem;line-height:1.6;overflow-x:auto;"><code>// Java (Spring Boot) &mdash; Decode and write to response
String acsBase64 = response.getResult().getAcsTemplate();

// Step 1: Decode from Base64
byte[] decodedBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(acsBase64);
String decodedHtml = new String(decodedBytes, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);

// Step 2: Write HTML to HttpServletResponse
httpResponse.setContentType("text/html;charset=UTF-8");
httpResponse.getWriter().write(decodedHtml);
httpResponse.getWriter().flush();</code></pre>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Important notes -->
                        <div class="sm-info-box" style="margin-top:1.5rem;border-left:4px solid #ff9800;padding:0.75rem 1rem;background:rgba(255,152,0,0.06);">
                            <strong style="color:#e65100;">&#9888; Important Notes</strong>
                            <ul style="margin:0.5rem 0 0;padding-left:1.25rem;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.9rem;">
                                <li><strong>Do NOT render in iframe</strong> &mdash; Bank pages set <code>X-Frame-Options: DENY</code>, blocking iframe embedding. Always use <code>window.open()</code> or render on a full page.</li>
                                <li><strong>Auto-submit form</strong> &mdash; The decoded HTML contains a <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> with a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> that auto-submits. You do not need to manually submit anything.</li>
                                <li><strong>Callback URLs</strong> &mdash; After 3DS, the bank redirects to your <code>surl</code> (success) or <code>furl</code> (failure). Ensure these are set correctly in the payment request.</li>
                                <li><strong>pureS2SSupported</strong> &mdash; If <code>binData.pureS2SSupported = true</code>, you can also use the <strong>Native OTP</strong> method (Submit OTP API) instead of rendering the ACS template. Both options work.</li>
                                <li><strong>Always present</strong> &mdash; The <code>acsTemplate</code> is returned in S2S flows regardless of <code>pureS2SSupported</code> value. It&rsquo;s the universal fallback for 3DS authentication.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div><!-- /sm-cards-acs-tool -->

